        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 5:19PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 519 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Beech Grove, or 11 miles northwest of Shelbyville.
This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Indianapolis, Greenwood, Fairland, and Boggstown.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 65 between mile markers 98 and 101.
Interstate 74 between mile markers 97 and 108.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
